                                        2274,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Manhattan world. Coughlan et al. [12] proposed the Manhattan world for human navigation on the basis of the prior over edge models. The Manhattan world assumption regards the world as consisting of grid- shaped roads; that is, two of the three orthogonal coordinate axes lie along a crossroads, and the remaining axis is vertical. Given the Manhattan world "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
